Girls are just as difficult for guys to understand as guys are difficult for girls to understand
09:03
We're just wired very, very differently
09:04
If I leave someone on "read", I'm almost never intentionally ignoring them. It's generally me forgetting to reply, or getting distracted, or trying to think of a goof reply
09:05
When I was courting a young woman named Ruthie, we would leave one another on read all the time. There was an understanding that we would be in contact each evening at the most, so we weren't too worried about it. It was a different dynamic than, say, my buddy Josh and myself, who often leave the other person on read without even a thumbs up. And it was certainly different than the once-a-week-or-so conversations I have with my friend Michelle
09:06
So it's quite possible that your fellow forgot or was distracted. Or perhaps he was not quite sure what to say.
